  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The governing requirement — that the relative hemolysis index RH must remain below 1.0 compared to the predicate device across all five flow-speed combinations — is documented inline within the package as a Requirement node; however, the top-level bindsRequirement link is intentionally absent in this Minimal-profile submission.",
