    "name": "Relative hemolysis index acceptance criterion",
    "description": "The CFD model shall predict a relative hemolysis index RH < 1.0 for each of the five flow-speed combinations evaluated, where RH is computed relative to the predicate device measured under identical in-vitro conditions. This requirement is traceable to FDA guidance on computational hemolysis assessment for Class II mechanical circulatory support devices.",
