      "rationale": "Validation and COU use the same pump geometry, the same blood species, and overlapping operating envelopes. Differences in anticoagulant concentration between validation (10 U/mL) and COU (8 U/mL heparin) assessed qualitatively as negligible for hemolysis outcomes. Formal equivalency quantification not required at MRL 2."
